<item>
            <title>[TIKA-1491] Identification of BPG (Better Portable Graphics) format</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-1491</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following the release of the &lt;a href=&quot;http://bellard.org/bpg/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;BPG (Better Portable Graphics)&lt;/a&gt; format a few days ago, I created the magic definitions for this format. See attached file. I&apos;ve tested this against the example files listed &lt;a href=&quot;http://fileformats.archiveteam.org/wiki/BPG&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that no officially registered MIME type exists for this format. I picked &lt;tt&gt;image/bpg&lt;/tt&gt; as this would be the most obvious choice, but I don&apos;t know if Tika sticks to any policy in such cases?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
