                            <comment id="14240534" author="gagravarr" created="Wed, 10 Dec 2014 02:21:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Normally the x- prefix is used for unofficial types, see &lt;a href=&quot;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045#section-6.3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045#section-6.3&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045#section-5.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2045#section-5.1&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2048#section-2.1.4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2048#section-2.1.4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following that approach would probably mean image/x-bpg for now, then image/bpg with an alias of image/x-bpg once the BPG community got the mimetype accepted&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyone know what other applications are using for now, and if the BPG community has plans to submit a registration request to the IETF any time soon?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14240976" author="johanvanderknijff" created="Wed, 10 Dec 2014 11:39:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Nick, following your suggestion I&apos;ve changed the mimetype to image/x-bpg, see updated attachment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14242394" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 11 Dec 2014 11:18:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, mime magic added in r1644596.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any chance you could also produce a small test .bpg file for us? Ideally with the same metadata as the .jpg file we have offers? We can then use that for a mime magic test, and later also have it ready for a .bpg parser test once there&apos;s a suitable Java BPG library to depend on&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
