                            <comment id="14242548" author="johanvanderknijff" created="Thu, 11 Dec 2014 14:09:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Based on the JPEG examples I created corresponding BPG files using libbpg (available at [&lt;a href=&quot;http://bellard.org/bpg/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://bellard.org/bpg/&lt;/a&gt;]). For each image I used the following command line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;bpgenc image.jpg -o image.bpg -keepmetadata&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Don&apos;t have the time now to check that all metadata are really preserved, but from a cursory glance in a hex editor I see the BPGs do contain XML formatted metadata and ICC profiles, possibly more. I zipped all the BPGs and added them as an attachment above. Hope this helps.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14244079" author="gagravarr" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2014 12:52:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test files added, along with a unit test, in r1644868. Thanks for the files!&lt;/p&gt;

